items.title: Books
items.description:
7 Days
A Novel by Debra Colby

Kate Morgan waits for her mother to return, knowing someday she will. The thought of it fills her with dread and anticipation. She hates and loves her mother, Meg Madison, in equal measures.

Kate has been raised by a man who is the only father she has ever known and a grandmother who will do anything to protect her granddaughter from the evil that she's fought against her entire life.

​When Meg finally does return, she has to face her demons and reveal the truth of her family's history in order to bring her daughter back to her. It takes only seven days to unravel the fragile threads that held their family together.

Click the link to watch the trailer for 7 Days.
https://youtu.be/0Ktnfnsbin8

user.about:
Author. 
I am not the most talented writer, but I have been told that my words "hit home." Which to me is a victory.  I write about "us." What we've been through and where we want to be. 

My most recent novel, 7 Days, tells the story of how life can change in a mere moment, leaving those behind with doubts and what-if’s. 

My previous novel, I Heard You, is a collection of short stories that I have heard over my 35 years in customer service. 

Mom’s Eye View is a compilation of articles that I wrote as a columnist for a local newspaper. This column ran for five years and was read by thousands. These stories revolve around a young wife and mother and the everyday trials that many young mothers go through; sometimes hectic, often emotional, but always trying to find the humor.
